    "created_at": "2016-02-04T20:05:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-02-04T20:05:32Z",
    "body": "First of all, I think you're mixing up unit tests and integration tests. You clearly don't want unit tests. You don't need user input for unit tests.\n\nIf you want to programmatically click/enter things in a `BrowserWindow`, use its `webContents` property - there's a `executeJavaScriptCode` method that will allow you to do exactly what you want. [Inject some JS](https://github.com/atom/electron/blob/master/docs/api/web-contents.md#webcontentsexecutejavascriptcode-usergesture) and have it click and enter things to your hearts content.\n\nSounds good?\n"
  },
